Mobile-first, fully responsive design. remember to use the mobile-first approach. 

favicon link source https://raw.githubusercontent.com/EIRSVi/eirsvi/refs/heads/docs/assets/image/288bc158-5999-425d-846e-4c0824f2294e.png 

Technology stack: strictly HTML, CSS, and JavaScript only. 
Prepare a professional, future-proof folder and file directory structure. such as components, pages, assets, styles, scripts, and static and more  for the future project.
 


Project Structure & Layouts:
- no color for header and footer style and make sure it fit screen size and responsive. their is not toolbar for navigation scroll down and up left and right.
- Centered, sticky icon navigation bar (Home | Article | Resource | Matrix | Sort)
A navbar that changes width on active page. 
Icons:
- Use Font Awesome icon font.
- all icons must be dark or black color.  
- Icons must be responsive and animated.
- icon hover must be emerald color.

  - Icons:
    - Home: <i class="fa-solid fa-house"></i>
    - Article: <i class="fa-solid fa-feather"></i>
    - Resource: <i class="fa-solid fa-passport"></i>
    - Matrix: <i class="fa-solid fa-shapes"></i>
    - Sort: <i class="fa-solid fa-signature"></i>
Navigation: 
- All navigation between menu/navbar links must be client-side (no page refresh).
- make sure mobile device responsive design
- show the menu navbar  on mobile devices or pc theme the same  as desktop theme layout.
-  make sure the menu navbar  is always visible. and don't show navbar title text below the icon. 
expected future edit:
- Home: Present bio and  etc.
- Article: Blog, writing, notes.
- Resource: Useful links, online courses, books.
- Matrix: Project demos, active projects, resources with difference categories type tap.
- Sort: List of ordinary profile people, relatives.


Typography:
- Fonts: Space Grotesk : default text in english, 
- JetBrains Mono: numeric and code style, 
- Noto Serif Khmer, Chenla: Khmer font. 
- all text must be dark or black color.
 




Footer: use Marquee style 
-Marquee  Animation:  social media icons (GitHub, X, TikTok, YouTube, Telegram) URL username: EIRSVi and copyright, EIRSVi 2025. 
- Uses  animation start from right to left and loop infinitely
- When marquee moves completely offscreen, resets to start
- always at the button of the page.
- make it smaller: 
- Pauses on hover, resumes when mouse leaves
- js key function : Marquee('.marquee', 0.4) // Selector and speed parameter
- example: when the user clicks on the social media icon, it will open a new tab with the URL. so the social media icon in marquee.    use color coCard2 


remember this design is for mobile first. 
Color System root:
- polynesian-blue: #164EA6ff; (hsl(217, 76%, 37%))
- jordy-blue: #8AB3F6ff; (hsl(217, 82%, 76%))

- mustard: #FED765ff; (hsl(47, 98%, 71%))
- jasmine: #FDE392ff; (hsl(48, 94%, 80%))

- emerald: #81CB94ff; (hsl(140, 44%, 65%))
- honeydew: #CEE9D6ff; (hsl(146, 47%, 86%))

Card Themes (Strict Rules):
1. Only use these card theme color pairs for backgrounds:
   - coCard1 (text: white): polynesian-blue, jordy-blue
   - coCard2 (text: black, bold): mustard, jasmine
   - coCard3 (text: black, links polynesian-blue): emerald, honeydew
2. Text color: only white or dark (black/near-black).
3. No gradients color  allowed.
4. No other background or accent colors permitted.
5. Links in coCard3: use polynesian-blue (#164EA6ff).
6. All UI elements must strictly follow these color rules.
7. All cards: 3px border radius. Allowed border colors for each card type:
   - coCard1: polynesian-blue (#164EA6ff) or jordy-blue (#8AB3F6ff)
   - coCard2: mustard (#FED765ff) or jasmine (#FDE392ff)
   - coCard3: emerald (#81CB94ff) or honeydew (#CEE9D6ff)

